than my rent alone she told the panel on monday 
the administration began the 800number service last october 
hoping to improve convenience and accessibility to the public by 
making phone representatives available for 12 hours per day 
instead of eight the system in which calls to local social 
security offices are routed to any of 37 national teleservice 
centers has been implemented so far in 60 percent of the nation 
and received 22 million calls 
the service was touted in two mailings to a total of 36 million 
beneficiaries in december and february 
lawmakers began hearing about the system after national busy 
signal rates reached 43 percent in january followed by 35 percent 
in february 
the rate dipped to 9 percent in march but only after calls 
dropped from 48 million in march to 34 million in february and 
after ssa brought in staff members in from other offices to answer 
calls a general accounting office official testified 
while the reassignment of staff contributed to the reduction 
of this busy signal rate for march it raises questions about the 
impact on the operations of the field facilities joseph delfico 
