<DOCNO> AP890411-0096 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
federal investigators on tuesday blamed 
inadequate track inspection and maintenance procedures by the 
burlington northern railroad for the derailment last summer of an 
amtrak passenger train in montana 
the train which was bound from chicago to seattle derailed 
aug 5 near saco mon when it struck track that had been warped 
by temperatures near 100 degrees the accident injured 165 people 
about a dozen of them seriously 
the national transportation safety board in its report on the 
accident said tuesday it was caused by shifting of track just ahead 
of the amtrak train the board said the shifting was caused by the 
intense heat but that track conditions and the danger of such 
buckling should have been apparent to burlington northern 
the probable cause of the accident said the safety board in its 
final report was burlington northerns inadequate track 
inspection and maintenance procedures which resulted in a thermally 
induced lateral shift of the track structure in front of the 
amtrak train 
the board continued that the lateral shift occurred when the 
train was closer than the 2478 feet necessary to bring the train 
to a safe stop the train was traveling at an authorized speed of 
79 miles an hour 
there was nothing that the engine crew could have done to 
have avoided or decreased the severity of the accident after they 
observed the shifted track said the report 
the derailment caused five of the trains cars to topple after 
leaving the tracks the 12car train was carrying 375 passengers 
and about a dozen crewmembers 
the safety board blamed some of the injuries on the lack of 
effective restraint devices that caused some items to fly around 
inside the cars while the board did not fault amtrak for the 
accident the report called on the passenger railroad to improve 
its training and procedures for evacuating passengers in such 
circumstances 
the safety board also called on burlington northern to improve 
its track inspection procedures and make available to inspectors 
devices that could determine when excessive heat might cause track 
to warp 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

