<TEXT>
despite two tests that seem to confirm part of 
a utah cold nuclear fusion experiment experts said tuesday that 
more questions need to be answered before most scientists accept 
there has been a breakthrough 
were all mystified by this and watching it said dale m 
meade head of fusion reaction research at princeton niversity 
its the scientific way to be skeptical that process is still 
going on 
meade and others said the experiments announced monday at texas 
aampm and georgia tech did shed some light on what university of utah 
officials claim is a demonstration of fusion at room temperature 
but most experts remain unconvinced that fusion has actually 
taken place and some suggest the phenomenon may be something new to 
science 
they utah researchers have taken the position that it was a 
fusion reaction said john soures a university of rochester 
fusion scientist but that has yet to proven 
i think this whole thing may go down as one of the most 
bizarre episodes in 20th century science he added 
in an announcement two weeks ago stanley pons of the university 
of utah and martin fleischmann of the university of southhampton in 
england said they had achieved fusion using ordinary laboratory 
equipment at room temperature 
their experiment used a rod of palladium and a coil of platinum 
immersed in a beaker of deuterium an isotope of hydrogen commonly 
found in seawater pons said that when electrical power was applied 
to the coil for about 100 hours it forced deuterium atoms into the 
palladium until they finally fused producing energy in the form of 
heat 
pons claimed the device made four watts of energy for every watt 
of energy used 
fusion has been the goal of thousands of scientists around the 
world for more than a quarter century it is the energy secret of 
the stars the sun and the reaction that gives the boom to the 
hydrogen bomb 
if the reaction could be controlled scientists believe it could 
be the ultimate energy source giving virtually limitless 
electrical power using a cheap fuel extracted from sea water and 
producing only modest amounts of radiation hazard 
in fusion hydrogen atoms are forced together as they fuse 
they give off energy neutrons and helium3 a stable chemical 
fusion is the opposite of fission the nuclear reaction that splits 
the atomic nucleus fission is the force that powers atomic power 
plants and nuclear bombs 
at texas aampm scientists said monday an apparatus similar to the 
utah experiment did produce some excess energy but the reaction 
was so small that their equipment was not sensitive enough to 
detect the flow of neutrons a characteristic of fusion 
aampms charles martin said his group could have come from some 
unusual chemical process and not from nuclear fusion this 
possibility he said is being investigated 
a similar experiment at georgia tech did produce neutrons 
causing researcher bill livesay to announce theres no question 
its fusion i still dont believe it even though i see it 
the georgia tech experiment began producing neutron particles 
and probes measured a flow of about 560 neutrons an hour above the 
background radiation 
however georgia techs james mahaffey said the team did not 
confirm that the experiment produced more energy than it used 
meade said fusion cannot be confirmed until more laboratories 
have conducted the experiment and made precise measurements of both 
the heat production and the flow of neutrons he said the rise in 
neutrons and in heat should track each other that is show by 
measurement to be directly related 
it is not enough to just see some heat there and the hint of a 
few neutrons said meade we need to be able to relate this 
energy to some process that would produce it 
he said the amount of energy reported in the utah experiment 
would develop trillions of neutrons a second and if the texas and 
georgia experiments matched the energy output they too would 
have high neutron flow 
they are missing billions of neutrons per second said 
meade they hypothize that is may a different type of nuclear 
reaction than we have known physics experts around the world are 
trying to come up with some nuclear reaction that we havent seen 
before it possible but not very probable 
both meade and soures said the energy surge seen in the 
experiment may be created by a battery effect 
it takes weeks for the energy output to get up to the reported 
levels said soures this suggests that its operating more 
like a battery than fusion 
he said the device could be storing the electrical energy put 
into the experiment and then discharging the power as heat when it 
becomes satuated 
tom dolan of the department of energy laboratory in idaho falls 
idaho said that a good explanation of the utah experiment will not 
be developed until more experiments are conducted and the 
fundamental process is finally understood 
sometimes these things could drag on for months before they 
are resolved he said but right now i dont think it is a 
breakthrough that will be useful 
</TEXT>
