forces and that role is not one of a policeman watching the 
country but to support the reign of law and the institutional 
order 
opposition leaders have denounced what the military calls the 
institutional order based on a 1980 constitution approved in a 
referendum 
opponents have centered their criticism on two issues a 
constitutional article that allows pinochet and the heads of the 
other military branches to remain as commanders until 1998 and the 
creation of a militarydominated national security council to 
represent its views on crucial matters 
no significant progress has been reported in negotiations 
between the government and opposition on possible constitutional 
changes 
