everything is under discussion 
actually the details of the tax package and specific spending 
decisions would be left for later 
the negotiators have been working to produce a very broad set of 
guidelines setting forth total figures for a handful of revenue 
and spending categories it would be left for the normal 
legislative process to produce the steps to enact those totals 
participants in the talks said they were sworn to secrecy about 
the specifics because of the sensitivity of the current 
discussions on possible cuts in bushs 300 billion defense budget 
and in domestic programs 
bush proposed that military spending be allowed to grow with 
inflation democratic negotiators have asked for slower defense 
growth so that more domestic demands can be met 
if the negotiators complete a package the house and senate 
budget committees would then draft more detailed spending plans for 
each chamber to consider then the two chambers would need to 
approve a single compromise plan 
the budget serves as the guide for annual spending bills and tax 
legislation for the new fiscal year which begins oct 1 
if congress and the president dont enact legislation to reduce 
the deficit to within 10 billion of the 100 billion goal the 
administration is required under the grammrudman law to order 
acrosstheboard spending cuts to make up the difference 
